# Whitelist approach: ignore EVERYTHING, then allow only the files meant to be published.
# This guarantees the confidential "wingrep context/" material, local config, and
# working notes can never be committed, even with `git add -A`.
/*
!/index.html
!/wingrep-webinar.html
!/wingrep-assets.js
!/wingrep-demo-data.js
!/README.md
!/.gitignore
# Fictional webinar demo kit (transcripts, prompt library); contains no real customer or company data.
!/webinar-demo/
!/webinar-demo/**
